  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Manager",
  "description": "<ul><li>Report to the Project Manager, over all in charge of site coordination.</li><li>Lead a team of operation staff in daily operations, manage and oversee the day-to-day construction activities of the project.</li><li>Maintain site access throughout the construction period.</li><li>Planning to prevent the problem on-site before it occurs, planning the delivery and storage of equipment and materials.</li><li>Ensure the progress of work is within budget and timelines as well as quality and safety objectives.</li><li>Control and monitor work progress and resources, monitor and control material wastage.</li><li>Carry out work scheduling, material requisition planning, project coordination, and documentation.</li><li>Responsible for on-site production scheduling and allocation of personnel and labour, arranging materials and mechanical equipment for each phase, directing and organizing solutions to various on-site issues, and handling emergencies and labour disputes at the construction site.</li><li>Responsible for organizing the preparation of construction organization designs, progress plans, safety technical measures, etc., primarily focusing on controlling the overall project timeline.</li><li>Responsible for coordinating the working relationships with company functional departments, subcontractors, material suppliers, etc.</li><li>Responsible for the management, coordination, evaluation, and assessment of the project department staff as per the branch office's requirements.</li><li>Perform any other duties as assigned from Management.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must pass at least a Degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent. Diploma holders or equivalent with relevant experience BSc/BA in Engineering (Civil) or Engineering or relevant field</li><li>8 years' experience in Site Management</li></ul>",
